<font color="#FF0000">TO JERRY CLARK</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jan 18  2:17:02 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
To Jerry Clark                                                                                                               You can keep beating your self up but what good is that doing you. You didn't make those kids do that to you. They made you do that to them. As for your crewmen. You couldn't save them. It was thier time. We're all sorry for that.                                                                      You where leading a soldiers life then. These are the things that happen to soldiers. It happened to me and my father. I haven't forgotten them in twenty six years and my father hasn't forgotten in fifty three years. We (that includes you) lived a soldiers life then. Not now.                                                                            Don't try to forget. You can't and shuoldn't. You can stop blaming yourself. I don't think you did anything wrong. You just happen to be the one that was there.                                                                                 I know it's easy to say &quot;don't blame yourself&quot; but what good has it done up to now?                                                                                                             Glad your home.                                             May peace be yours.                                           Fez
